%T A396008 42,1029,2050,260,265,513,290,549,64,65,66,68,69,72,73,74,10241,80,81,
%U A396008 82,84,85,16393,2058,4100,2121,520,16905,530,545,2373,1026,580,585
%N A396008 a(n) = A396006(n)*A396007(n).
%C A396008 A number is fibbinary (A003714) if its base-2 representation contains no occurrence of 11.  For each j we can ask if there is a representation of the form j = A/B with both A and B fibbinary.   Sequence A396006 lists those representable j.  Sequence A396007 lists the corresponding B for those j, while this sequence lists the corresponding A.
%H A396008 J. V. F. Meleshko, <a href="http://hdl.handle.net/10012/18952">Automata and ratio sets</a>, Master's thesis, University of Waterloo, 2022.
%Y A396008 Cf. A003714, A395143, A396006, A396007.
%K A396008 nonn,new
%O A396008 1,2
